        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/8–1845</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Balfour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Acting Secretary of State presents his compliments to the British Chargé
                    d’Affaires and refers to the Embassy’s note of August 18, 1945 dealing with the
                    Committee to study the procedure for the dismemberment of Germany, which was
                    established at the Crimea Conference.</p>
                <p>The United States Government is in agreement with His Majesty’s Government that
                    there is no need for this Committee to proceed with the work allotted to it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-06">September 6,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
